Royal Palm SavingsAssociation said it has entered into an agreement with theFederal Home Loan Bank Board and the Florida Department ofBanking and Finance resulting in the removal of limitationswhich had severely restricted its growth and lending.    The company said it will now be permitted to grow about 70mln dlrs in calendar 1987, or about 15 pct for this year, andat the same rate thereafter.    Royal Palm said under the accord, it will resume commercialand nonresidential lending but will place substantial emphasison residential loans.    The company said it agreed to adopt new policies andprocedures but did not elaborate. Reuter&#3;